    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're building a program to help students stay hydrated throughout the school day. You want the reminder to pop up after each class period. Instead of writing the same message over and over, you'll define a function once and call it multiple times.\r\n\r\n1. Define a function called `remind_to_drink()` that prints a message encouraging someone to drink water.\r\n\r\n2. Call the function **five times** to represent five class periods.\r\n\r\n3. Make sure the reminder prints five times in a row.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nWriting your message once in a function and calling it repeatedly keeps your code clean and easy to update. If the message ever changes, you’ll only need to change it in one place.\r\n\r\nUse the **UMPIRE** strategy to understand what's happening, make a plan, test your output, and explain your thinking.",
